<subSubSection id="C3266529FFAEFFBBFF5CFA94DA9DFAD0" box="[151,732,1338,1365]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CFA94DA9DFAD0" blockId="16.[151,732,1338,1365]" box="[151,732,1338,1365]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<heading id="D0CB81CEFFAEFFBBFF5CFA94DA9DFAD0" bold="true" box="[151,732,1338,1365]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFF5CFA94DA9DFAD0" bold="true" box="[151,732,1338,1365]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
Key to the Malagasy species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAEFFBBFDD6FA94DA9DFAD0" authorityName="Eggers" authorityYear="1920" box="[541,732,1338,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFDD6FA94DA9DFAD0" bold="true" box="[541,732,1338,1365]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">Pseudomicracis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<key id="FFAD6193FFAEFFBAFF5CFAD1DDDCFC31" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="342" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<subSubSection id="C3266529FFAEFFBBFF5CFAD1DDDDFA69" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" type="key">
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAEFFBBFF5CFAD1DDDDFA69" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CFAD1DDDDFA37" blockId="16.[151,1437,1407,1517]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CFAD1DDDDFA37" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">1 Antennal scapus small, rounded, with few setae; most species with interstrial setae truncated, many species with rugose to granulated interstriae on posterior part of elytra, some of these with larger tubercles (males).......................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CFA14DDDDFA69" blockId="16.[151,1437,1407,1517]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CFA14DDDDFA69" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">- Scapus triangularly extended dorsally, sometimes more strongly elongated into a spike; interstrial setae spatulate, rarely truncated; elytral cuticle generally smooth (females)........................................................... 11</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3266529FFAEFFBAFF5CF9B5DDDCFC31" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="342" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF9B5D89AF9B0" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,219,1563,1589]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">Males</paragraph>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAEFFBBFF5CF993DDDDF908" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF993DDDDF9EA" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF993DDDDF9EA" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">2 Posterolateral margin of declivity with a series of large tubercles, each much larger than antennal club, declivity flattened; antennal club&gt;1.5 × longer than wide, sutures obscure....................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF9D6DDDDF908" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1655,1677]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF9D6DDDDF908" box="[151,1436,1655,1677]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">- Elytral declivity smooth or at most with posterolateral rim of small granules; antennal club &lt;1.3× as long as wide........ 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAEFFBBFF5CF93BDDDDF942" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF93BDDDDF92F" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1684,1706]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF93BDDDDF92F" box="[151,1436,1684,1706]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
3 One pair of tall, narrow ridges on lower two thirds of declivity located on interstriae 4–5.................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAEFFBBFAFCF93BDDDDF92F" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1335,1436,1685,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pennata">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFAFCF93BDDDDF92F" box="[1335,1436,1685,1706]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">P. pennata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF91CDDDDF942" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1714,1736]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF91CDDDDF942" box="[151,1436,1714,1736]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">- Posterolateral margin of declivity with a series of nodules..................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAEFFBBFF5CF961DDDDF884" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF961DDDDF961" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1743,1765]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF961DDDDF961" box="[151,1436,1743,1765]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
4 Declivital margin with 6–7 subequal nodules..................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAEFFBBFAD6F97EDDDDF961" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[1309,1436,1743,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomicoides">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFAD6F97EDDDDF961" box="[1309,1436,1743,1765]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">P. tomicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF943DDDDF884" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1772,1794]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF943DDDDF884" box="[151,1436,1772,1794]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
- Declivital margin with 2–3 much larger nodules on interstriae 4–6........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAEFFBBFA8CF943DDDDF884" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[1351,1436,1772,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFA8CF943DDDDF884" box="[1351,1436,1772,1794]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">P. dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAEFFBBFF5CF8A4DDDDF8DF" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF8A4DDDDF8B9" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF8A4DDDDF8B9" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
5 Elytral interstriae coarsely granulated or tuberculate, interstrial setae curved and spatulate; stout species, &lt;2.5 × as long as wide.............................................................................. 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFB07F886DD0BF8B8" box="[1228,1354,1832,1853]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAEFFBBFB07F886DD07F8B8" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1228,1350,1832,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrucosa" status="sp. nov.">P. verrucosa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFA9BF889DDDDF8B9" bold="true" box="[1360,1436,1831,1852]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFAEFFBBFA9BF889DDDDF8B9" box="[1360,1436,1831,1852]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF8EBDDDDF8DF" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1860,1882]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF8EBDDDDF8DF" box="[151,1436,1860,1882]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">- Elytral interstriae at most only finely granulated and rugose, setae erect, truncated; body&gt;2.6 × as long as wide.......... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAEFFBBFF5CF8CCDDDDF810" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF8CCDDDDF8F2" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1890,1912]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF8CCDDDDF8F2" box="[151,1436,1890,1912]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
6 Posterolateral margin of declivity with a granulated rim; elytral apex very broadly mucronate........ 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFB1DF8CCDD0BF8F2" box="[1238,1354,1890,1911]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAEFFBBFB1DF8CCDD07F8F2" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1238,1350,1890,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronata" status="sp. nov.">P. coronata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFA9BF8CCDDDDF8F2" bold="true" box="[1360,1436,1890,1911]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFAEFFBBFA9BF8CCDDDDF8F2" box="[1360,1436,1890,1911]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF82EDDDDF810" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1919,1941]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF82EDDDDF810" box="[151,1436,1919,1941]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">- Declivital margin smooth; elytral apex narrowly mucronate................................................... 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAEFFBBFF5CF833DDDDF84A" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF833DDDDF837" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1948,1970]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF833DDDDF837" box="[151,1436,1948,1970]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">7 Anterior margin of pronotum with 4–6 narrowly separated raised teeth.......................................... 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF814DDDDF84A" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,1978,2000]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF814DDDDF84A" box="[151,1436,1978,2000]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">- Anterior margin of pronotum smooth or with scant irregular granules........................................... 10</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAEFFBAFF5CF879DDDDFF28" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="342" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAEFFBBFF5CF879DDDDF869" blockId="16.[151,1437,1563,2029]" box="[151,1436,2007,2029]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAEFFBBFF5CF879DDDDF869" box="[151,1436,2007,2029]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
8 Antennal club with only weakly procurved sutures.............................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAEFFBBFACFF876DD05F868" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1284,1348,2008,2029]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFACFF876DD05F868" box="[1284,1348,2008,2029]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">P. atra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAEFFBBFA9BF879DDDDF869" bold="true" box="[1360,1436,2007,2028]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFAEFFBBFA9BF879DDDDF869" box="[1360,1436,2007,2028]" pageId="16" pageNumber="341" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFF36DDDDFF28" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,378]" box="[151,1436,151,173]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFF36DDDDFF28" box="[151,1436,151,173]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">- Antennal club with strongly procurved sutures.............................................................. 9</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAFFFBAFF5CFF1BDDDDFEA7" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFF1BDDDDFF62" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,378]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFF1BDDDDFF62" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
9 Interstrial setae uniseriate, interstriae 1 with only broad scale-like setae; eyes separated above by 2.5 × their width............................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFB1FFF7DDD05FF62" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1236,1348,210,232]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lauricola" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFB1FFF7DDD05FF62" box="[1236,1348,210,232]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">P. lauricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFA9BFF7CDDDDFF62" bold="true" box="[1360,1436,210,231]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFAFFFBAFA9BFF7CDDDDFF62" box="[1360,1436,210,231]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFF5EDDDDFEA7" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,378]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFF5EDDDDFEA7" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
- Interstrial setae slightly confused, interstriae 1 with broad scale-like setae and fine setae along the suture which are similar to those in striae; eyes separated above by &lt;2× their width........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFB3AFEA3DD05FEA7" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1265,1348,269,290]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFB3AFEA3DD05FEA7" box="[1265,1348,269,290]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">P. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFA9BFEA3DDDDFEA7" bold="true" box="[1360,1436,269,290]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFAFFFBAFA9BFEA3DDDDFEA7" box="[1360,1436,269,290]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAFFFBAFF5CFE84DDDDFEFF" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFE84DDDDFEBA" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,378]" box="[151,1436,298,320]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFE84DDDDFEBA" box="[151,1436,298,320]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
10 Eyes normal, separated above by about 3 × their width; all interstriae with uniseriate setae........... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFB1CFE85DDDDFEBA" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[1239,1436,298,320]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFB1CFE85DDDDFEBA" box="[1239,1436,298,320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">P. madagascariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFEE6DDDDFEFF" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,378]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFEE6DDDDFEFF" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
- Eyes large, separated above by &lt;1.5 × their width; interstria 1 with confused setae, other interstriae uniseriate............................................................................................. 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFB77FECBDD0BFEFF" box="[1212,1354,357,378]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFB77FECBDD07FEFF" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1212,1350,357,378]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitrioculata" status="sp. nov.">P. vitrioculata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFA9BFECBDDDDFEFF" bold="true" box="[1360,1436,357,378]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFAFFFBAFA9BFECBDDDDFEFF" box="[1360,1436,357,378]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFE07D8B5FE46" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,244,425,451]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">Females</paragraph>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAFFFBAFF5CFE64DDDDFD9F" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFE64DDDDFE5A" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,458,480]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFE64DDDDFE5A" box="[151,1436,458,480]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">11 Antennal club elongated, sutures obscure; body &lt;2.6 × as long as wide......................................... 12</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFE46DDDDFD9F" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFE46DDDDFD9F" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">- Antennal club only slightly longer than broad, with two distinctly procurved sutures marked by setae; body&gt;2.7 × as long as wide.............................................................................................. 14</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAFFFBAFF5CFD8CDDDDFDF7" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFD8CDDDDFDD0" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFD8CDDDDFDD0" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
12 Setae on elytral interstriae and posterior part of pronotum dagger-shaped; mucro on elytral apex in lateral view taller than long....................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFAFCFDEEDDDDFDD0" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1335,1436,576,597]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pennata">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFAFCFDEEDDDDFDD0" box="[1335,1436,576,597]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">P. pennata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFDF3DDDDFDF7" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,605,627]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFDF3DDDDFDF7" box="[151,1436,605,627]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">- Setae either bristle-like or spatulate; mucro longer than tall................................................... 13</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAFFFBAFF5CFDD4DDDDFD4F" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFDD4DDDDFD0A" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,634,656]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFDD4DDDDFD0A" box="[151,1436,634,656]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
13 Frons densely setose, setae long; sutures on antennal club not visible; setae on declivital interstriae confused.. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFAD6FDD5DDDDFD0A" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[1309,1436,634,656]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomicoides">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFAD6FDD5DDDDFD0A" box="[1309,1436,634,656]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">P. tomicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFD36DDDDFD4F" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFD36DDDDFD4F" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
- Frons with short and well separated setae; sutures on club obscurely marked, procurved; setae on declivital interstriae uniseriate.......................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFA8CFD1BDDDDFD4F" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[1351,1436,693,714]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFA8CFD1BDDDDFD4F" box="[1351,1436,693,714]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">P. dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAFFFBAFF5CFD7CDDDDFC80" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFD7CDDDDFD62" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,722,744]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFD7CDDDDFD62" box="[151,1436,722,744]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
14 Frons lightly concave, along dorsal margin with a broad projecting tuft of setae................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFB1CFD7DDDDDFD62" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[1239,1436,722,744]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFB1CFD7DDDDDFD62" box="[1239,1436,722,744]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">P. madagascariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFD5EDDDDFC80" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,751,773]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFD5EDDDDFC80" box="[151,1436,751,773]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">- Frons flattened or convex, vestiture scant................................................................. 15</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAFFFBAFF5CFCA3DDDDFCC5" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFCA3DDDDFCA7" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,781,803]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFCA3DDDDFCA7" box="[151,1436,781,803]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
15 Interstrial and strial setae confused on and near interstriae 1..................................... 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFB3AFCA3DD0BFCA7" box="[1265,1354,781,802]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFB3AFCA3DD07FCA7" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1265,1350,781,802]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa" status="sp. nov.">P. pilosa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFA9BFCA3DDDDFCA7" bold="true" box="[1360,1436,781,802]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFAFFFBAFA9BFCA3DDDDFCA7" box="[1360,1436,781,802]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFC85DDDDFCC5" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,810,832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFC85DDDDFCC5" box="[151,1436,810,832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">- All strial and interstrial setae in uniseriate rows............................................................ 16</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAFFFBAFF5CFCE9DDDDFCFF" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFCE9DDDDFCD8" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,839,862]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFCE9DDDDFCD8" box="[151,1436,839,862]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
16 Elytral apex (mucro) extended, base of mucro very broad, almost half the with of elytra............. 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFB1DFCE6DD0BFCD8" box="[1238,1354,840,861]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFB1DFCE6DD07FCD8" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1238,1350,840,861]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronata" status="sp. nov.">P. coronata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFA9BFCE6DDDDFCD8" bold="true" box="[1360,1436,840,861]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFAFFFBAFA9BFCE6DDDDFCD8" box="[1360,1436,840,861]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFCCBDDDDFCFF" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,869,891]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFCCBDDDDFCFF" box="[151,1436,869,891]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">- Elytral apex not extended, base of mucro about one-quarter as wide as elytra..................................... 17</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C82E07FFAFFFBAFF5CFC2CDDDCFC31" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFC2CDDDDFC12" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1436,898,920]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFC2CDDDDFC12" box="[151,1436,898,920]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
17 Scapus extended dorsally into a short spike; interstrial setae equally distributed from base to apex of elytra..... 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFB12FC2DDD0DFC12" box="[1241,1356,898,920]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFB12FC2DDD09FC12" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1241,1352,898,920]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lauricola" status="sp. nov.">P. lauricola</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFA9AFC2CDDDDFC12" bold="true" box="[1361,1436,898,919]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFAFFFBAFA9AFC2CDDDDFC12" box="[1361,1436,898,919]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFAFFFBAFF5CFC0EDDDCFC31" blockId="17.[151,1437,425,949]" box="[151,1437,927,949]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
<keyLead id="30CD9597FFAFFFBAFF5CFC0EDDDCFC31" box="[151,1437,927,949]" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">
- Scapus triangular, not taller than long; interstrial setae mainly on declivity................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFAFFFBAFAFDFC0EDDDCFC31" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1334,1437,927,949]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFAFFFBAFAFDFC0EDDDCFC31" box="[1334,1437,927,949]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="342">P. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
